node-globby (11.0.1+~cs16.18.31-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Team upload

  [ Debian Janitor ]
  * Trim trailing whitespace.
  * Use secure copyright file specification URI.
  * Set upstream metadata fields: Bug-Database, Bug-Submit, Repository,
    Repository-Browse.

  [ Xavier Guimard ]
  * Bump debhelper compatibility level to 13
  * Declare compliance with policy 4.5.0
  * Add "Rules-Requires-Root: no"
  * Add debian/gbp.conf
  * Use dh-sequence-nodejs auto install
  * New upstream version 11.0.1+~cs16.18.31
    Embed components:
    + dir-glob
    + fast-glob
    + fastq
    + merge2
    + reusify
    + run-parallel
    + @nodelib/fs.scandir
    + @nodelib/fs.stat
    + @nodelib/fs.walk
    + @nodelib/fs.macchiato
    Really: 11.0.1+~3.0.1+~3.2.4+~1.8.0+~1.4.1+~1.0.4+~1.1.9+~2.1.3+~2.0.3
            +~1.2.4+~1.0.2
  * Embed some missing @types declaration for build only
  * Update copyright
  * Update build
  * Enable upstream test using tape instead of ava
  * Update dependencies:
    + remove      : node-arrify, node-pify
    + add         : node-glob-parent, node-ignore, node-micromatch
    + build-depend: mocha, node-ci-info, node-sinon, node-tape,
                    node-typescript, node-typescript-types
  * Indicates that this version breaks node-copy-webpack-plugin < 4.3.0-9~

